#    .        visits  
#       :   --   , 
#      ( 'start_ts' / 'uid'),   --
#  ,        ('source_id' / 'device'), 
#   --      ('session_date' / 'session_week' /
# 'session_month',   --      ('' / '' / ''))

def metric_ill(wut, subj, div, name):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,9))
    if wut == 'uid':
        z = visits.groupby([subj, div])[wut].nunique().reset_index()
        sns.barplot(x=subj, y=wut, data=z, capsize=0.05, ax=ax)
        if subj == 'source_id': 
            plt.xlabel('  ')
            plt.ylabel(' ')
            plt.title('    '+name)
        if subj == 'device':
            plt.xlabel(' ')
            plt.ylabel(' ')
            plt.title('    '+name)
    if wut == 'start_ts':
        z = visits.groupby([subj, div])[wut].count().reset_index()
        sns.barplot(x=subj, y=wut, data=z, capsize=0.05, ax=ax)
        if subj == 'source_id': 
            plt.xlabel('  ')
            plt.ylabel('')
            plt.title('    '+name)
        if subj == 'device':
            plt.xlabel(' ')
            plt.ylabel('')
            plt.title('    '+name)
    plt.show()
